WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.440 align:middle line:90%
[WHOOSH]

00:00:02.440 --> 00:00:04.392 align:middle line:90%


00:00:04.392 --> 00:00:06.832 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:06.832 --> 00:00:19.520 align:middle line:90%


00:00:19.520 --> 00:00:22.040 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA GARR: Everything we
do is based on the agreements

00:00:22.040 --> 00:00:23.570 align:middle line:90%
that we have made.

00:00:23.570 --> 00:00:25.280 align:middle line:10%
If it's agreements
with ourselves

00:00:25.280 --> 00:00:29.600 align:middle line:10%
or other people
or God or life, we

00:00:29.600 --> 00:00:33.290 align:middle line:10%
have set it up at some point.

00:00:33.290 --> 00:00:35.870 align:middle line:84%
So what if we were to
do this intentionally,

00:00:35.870 --> 00:00:38.390 align:middle line:84%
like Don Miguel Ruiz
suggests in his book

00:00:38.390 --> 00:00:40.640 align:middle line:84%
"The Four Agreements,"
which, by the way,

00:00:40.640 --> 00:00:44.630 align:middle line:84%
it spent almost a decade on "The
New York Times" bestseller list

00:00:44.630 --> 00:00:47.660 align:middle line:90%
and sold over 7 million copies.

00:00:47.660 --> 00:00:49.880 align:middle line:84%
Based on the ancient
Toltec wisdom,

00:00:49.880 --> 00:00:53.120 align:middle line:84%
"The Four Agreements" offers
a powerful code of conduct

00:00:53.120 --> 00:00:55.850 align:middle line:84%
that can rapidly
transform our lives

00:00:55.850 --> 00:00:59.570 align:middle line:84%
to a new experience of
freedom, of true happiness,

00:00:59.570 --> 00:01:02.240 align:middle line:90%
and of ultimately love.

00:01:02.240 --> 00:01:05.750 align:middle line:84%
I am so honored to be welcomed
here by Don Miguel Ruiz.

00:01:05.750 --> 00:01:07.985 align:middle line:84%
Thank you so much
for being here.

00:01:07.985 --> 00:01:10.160 align:middle line:84%
>>DON MIGUEL RUIZ:
Well, it is my pleasure.

00:01:10.160 --> 00:01:12.650 align:middle line:90%
It's great to meet you.

00:01:12.650 --> 00:01:14.210 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Absolutely.

00:01:14.210 --> 00:01:15.320 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:01:15.320 --> 00:01:18.990 align:middle line:84%
We have spent time together
at some incredible moments

00:01:18.990 --> 00:01:19.790 align:middle line:90%
in my life.

00:01:19.790 --> 00:01:22.810 align:middle line:84%
I remember there was once we
were at a conference together,

00:01:22.810 --> 00:01:24.560 align:middle line:84%
and there was an
exercise where we are all

00:01:24.560 --> 00:01:27.110 align:middle line:90%
giving each other hugs.

00:01:27.110 --> 00:01:31.340 align:middle line:84%
And out of all the people
that I was hugging,

00:01:31.340 --> 00:01:34.520 align:middle line:84%
I got a hug from you
and I burst into tears

00:01:34.520 --> 00:01:40.490 align:middle line:84%
because you showed me
what pure love felt like.

00:01:40.490 --> 00:01:42.020 align:middle line:90%
I will always remember that.

00:01:42.020 --> 00:01:46.430 align:middle line:84%
You really represent that
heart-opening incredible pure

00:01:46.430 --> 00:01:47.360 align:middle line:90%
love.

00:01:47.360 --> 00:01:49.880 align:middle line:84%
So I know that people
will be able to feel that

00:01:49.880 --> 00:01:52.595 align:middle line:84%
by listening to our interview
today, so thank you.

00:01:52.595 --> 00:01:54.770 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Well,
you're very welcome.

00:01:54.770 --> 00:01:57.200 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You experienced
that all day, don't you?

00:01:57.200 --> 00:01:58.000 align:middle line:90%
Do you?

00:01:58.000 --> 00:02:02.930 align:middle line:10%
>>RUIZ: Well, I am love,
but you are also love.

00:02:02.930 --> 00:02:07.200 align:middle line:10%
And everybody is love,
they just don't know.

00:02:07.200 --> 00:02:09.199 align:middle line:90%
But they are.

00:02:09.199 --> 00:02:11.750 align:middle line:84%
Well, like I say, they
just don't believe it.

00:02:11.750 --> 00:02:13.250 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: There's a
lot of things that

00:02:13.250 --> 00:02:15.140 align:middle line:84%
knock us off that love,
though, Don Miguel.

00:02:15.140 --> 00:02:16.220 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: Sure.

00:02:16.220 --> 00:02:17.840 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: A lot of
challenges, a lot

00:02:17.840 --> 00:02:21.530 align:middle line:84%
of wrongness, a lot of
hurt, which brings me

00:02:21.530 --> 00:02:22.712 align:middle line:90%
to "The Four Agreements."

00:02:22.712 --> 00:02:24.170 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Well, that's
the reason why

00:02:24.170 --> 00:02:30.670 align:middle line:84%
I create this book, to solve
a problem that we all have,

00:02:30.670 --> 00:02:34.325 align:middle line:84%
and that problem is
the domestication.

00:02:34.325 --> 00:02:35.200 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What is that?

00:02:35.200 --> 00:02:36.605 align:middle line:90%
What is domestication?

00:02:36.605 --> 00:02:39.500 align:middle line:90%


00:02:39.500 --> 00:02:42.740 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Well, we are
animals, and we're

00:02:42.740 --> 00:02:47.000 align:middle line:90%
trained to please other people.

00:02:47.000 --> 00:02:47.800 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:02:47.800 --> 00:02:51.760 align:middle line:84%
They prepare us to
be part of society.

00:02:51.760 --> 00:02:58.230 align:middle line:84%
This society exists even
long before we was born.

00:02:58.230 --> 00:03:00.290 align:middle line:84%
And society is
changing all the time,

00:03:00.290 --> 00:03:04.610 align:middle line:84%
have all these rules, all
the laws, the ways you have

00:03:04.610 --> 00:03:07.430 align:middle line:90%
to behave, all those beliefs.

00:03:07.430 --> 00:03:09.390 align:middle line:90%
There's so many beliefs--

00:03:09.390 --> 00:03:15.050 align:middle line:84%
political beliefs, real
issues beliefs, sports.

00:03:15.050 --> 00:03:17.070 align:middle line:90%
It's all iterations.

00:03:17.070 --> 00:03:20.300 align:middle line:84%
It's something that
is already ongoing.

00:03:20.300 --> 00:03:23.560 align:middle line:90%
We personally didn't create it.

00:03:23.560 --> 00:03:25.470 align:middle line:90%
We was born here.

00:03:25.470 --> 00:03:29.600 align:middle line:84%
And when our brain was
getting more and more mature,

00:03:29.600 --> 00:03:32.750 align:middle line:84%
our parents hook our
attention and they start

00:03:32.750 --> 00:03:36.050 align:middle line:90%
teaching us what they know.

00:03:36.050 --> 00:03:39.330 align:middle line:84%
And what they know
is the society.

00:03:39.330 --> 00:03:43.520 align:middle line:84%
We go to school, and they
teach us also what they know.

00:03:43.520 --> 00:03:46.460 align:middle line:84%
They prepare us to be
part of that society,

00:03:46.460 --> 00:03:48.810 align:middle line:90%
and we believe everything.

00:03:48.810 --> 00:03:53.265 align:middle line:84%
We was domesticated to be
a human being according

00:03:53.265 --> 00:03:56.535 align:middle line:84%
to the idea of what
a human being is.

00:03:56.535 --> 00:03:57.410 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You're right.

00:03:57.410 --> 00:04:00.990 align:middle line:84%
We are people-pleasing
machines, aren't we?

00:04:00.990 --> 00:04:05.900 align:middle line:84%
From very early on, we want to
please our parents for love.

00:04:05.900 --> 00:04:08.870 align:middle line:84%
Our parents want us to
please them for love.

00:04:08.870 --> 00:04:13.190 align:middle line:84%
We go into society, we're
judged on our grades, what

00:04:13.190 --> 00:04:16.310 align:middle line:84%
we're asked to perform
at a certain level

00:04:16.310 --> 00:04:20.300 align:middle line:84%
in order to hit certain
markers in your childhood

00:04:20.300 --> 00:04:24.425 align:middle line:84%
and adolescence and adulthood
and work life and everything.

00:04:24.425 --> 00:04:26.315 align:middle line:90%
We are people-pleasing machines.

00:04:26.315 --> 00:04:29.730 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Yes, we are
domesticated animals,

00:04:29.730 --> 00:04:31.730 align:middle line:84%
and we produce
that domestication.

00:04:31.730 --> 00:04:38.100 align:middle line:84%
Well, we create a whole belief
system, very complicated,

00:04:38.100 --> 00:04:41.840 align:middle line:84%
and we adopt all the rules
that exist in society

00:04:41.840 --> 00:04:45.810 align:middle line:90%
and we apply it to ourself.

00:04:45.810 --> 00:04:50.990 align:middle line:84%
We have all the beliefs about
whatever religion we follow,

00:04:50.990 --> 00:04:54.260 align:middle line:84%
about all what we
say a little before.

00:04:54.260 --> 00:04:59.480 align:middle line:84%
But what about if it's
not true what we believe?

00:04:59.480 --> 00:05:00.530 align:middle line:90%
What about that?

00:05:00.530 --> 00:05:02.630 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yeah, that
blows your mind.

00:05:02.630 --> 00:05:04.910 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, it really
changes everything.

00:05:04.910 --> 00:05:06.050 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: Exactly.

00:05:06.050 --> 00:05:09.020 align:middle line:84%
Then with these
Four Agreements is

00:05:09.020 --> 00:05:12.500 align:middle line:84%
like a challenge to
everything that we

00:05:12.500 --> 00:05:16.940 align:middle line:84%
believe because we create all
those agreements to support

00:05:16.940 --> 00:05:18.880 align:middle line:90%
everything that we believe--

00:05:18.880 --> 00:05:23.560 align:middle line:84%
what is good, bad, right,
wrong, should be, shouldn't be.

00:05:23.560 --> 00:05:29.295 align:middle line:84%
We like to judge everybody, and
we judge ourself the same way.

00:05:29.295 --> 00:05:35.650 align:middle line:84%
We are the worst judge to
ourself than anybody else.

00:05:35.650 --> 00:05:40.630 align:middle line:84%
And we judge ourself according
to rules of the domestication

00:05:40.630 --> 00:05:42.020 align:middle line:90%
that we have.

00:05:42.020 --> 00:05:42.820 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:05:42.820 --> 00:05:45.790 align:middle line:84%
Society, performance,
all of these things.

00:05:45.790 --> 00:05:48.040 align:middle line:84%
So did "The Four
Agreements" come out

00:05:48.040 --> 00:05:54.880 align:middle line:84%
of your experience in being
raised in the Toltec way?

00:05:54.880 --> 00:05:56.740 align:middle line:84%
Did you come about
these four agreements

00:05:56.740 --> 00:05:58.610 align:middle line:84%
because of what you
were experiencing

00:05:58.610 --> 00:05:59.410 align:middle line:90%
with domestication?

00:05:59.410 --> 00:06:03.250 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: OK, let me tell
you how that happened.

00:06:03.250 --> 00:06:07.860 align:middle line:84%
I used to be a medical
doctor, a surgeon,

00:06:07.860 --> 00:06:10.150 align:middle line:84%
and I practiced dental
surgery with my brother,

00:06:10.150 --> 00:06:11.780 align:middle line:90%
who is an oral surgeon.

00:06:11.780 --> 00:06:16.720 align:middle line:84%
I was just a surgeon, but
I practiced a lot with him.

00:06:16.720 --> 00:06:21.880 align:middle line:84%
But in certain moment,
I see that the problem

00:06:21.880 --> 00:06:27.220 align:middle line:84%
is in the mind, not
in the physical body.

00:06:27.220 --> 00:06:28.780 align:middle line:84%
Then at that moment,
I really want

00:06:28.780 --> 00:06:32.710 align:middle line:84%
to understand how
the mind works.

00:06:32.710 --> 00:06:35.860 align:middle line:84%
Then I stop being
a medical doctor.

00:06:35.860 --> 00:06:41.320 align:middle line:84%
I went back to my mother, who
carried the Toltec knowledge,

00:06:41.320 --> 00:06:43.615 align:middle line:90%
and she becomes my mentor.

00:06:43.615 --> 00:06:46.400 align:middle line:90%


00:06:46.400 --> 00:06:50.830 align:middle line:84%
Then I didn't really
leave the medicine behind.

00:06:50.830 --> 00:06:53.080 align:middle line:90%
I just changed the direction.

00:06:53.080 --> 00:07:01.030 align:middle line:84%
I focus all my intention into
understand the human mind

00:07:01.030 --> 00:07:04.570 align:middle line:84%
until it was as
clear as water to me.

00:07:04.570 --> 00:07:06.880 align:middle line:84%
The I start working
with apprentices

00:07:06.880 --> 00:07:11.680 align:middle line:84%
for around 10 years, more
and more apprentices.

00:07:11.680 --> 00:07:14.230 align:middle line:84%
I create so many
different ways how

00:07:14.230 --> 00:07:18.460 align:middle line:84%
to study them, how to help
them in the integration

00:07:18.460 --> 00:07:23.350 align:middle line:84%
of their life, and the result,
it was "The Four Agreements."

00:07:23.350 --> 00:07:25.540 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Ah It's interesting
you came about it

00:07:25.540 --> 00:07:29.920 align:middle line:84%
from the opposite way
of looking at the mind

00:07:29.920 --> 00:07:33.340 align:middle line:84%
and looking at surgery
and looking at damage

00:07:33.340 --> 00:07:37.380 align:middle line:84%
and wondering where
did this start.

00:07:37.380 --> 00:07:39.790 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Then when
the mind becomes

00:07:39.790 --> 00:07:44.350 align:middle line:84%
to be like a clear
water, I see also

00:07:44.350 --> 00:07:48.490 align:middle line:84%
the solutions because I
understand the problem was

00:07:48.490 --> 00:07:50.860 align:middle line:90%
the human domestication.

00:07:50.860 --> 00:07:54.790 align:middle line:84%
And we want to be free
of that domestication.

00:07:54.790 --> 00:08:01.450 align:middle line:84%
Then four simple agreements
becomes the biggest challenge

00:08:01.450 --> 00:08:05.100 align:middle line:84%
to doubt about
everything that we know.

00:08:05.100 --> 00:08:07.940 align:middle line:84%
Well, in the beginning, it
was already five agreements,

00:08:07.940 --> 00:08:11.860 align:middle line:84%
but I decide to work only the
four ones because the fifth one

00:08:11.860 --> 00:08:15.230 align:middle line:84%
I thought it was too
much for anybody.

00:08:15.230 --> 00:08:20.160 align:middle line:84%
Anyway, years later, my son Jose
wrote "The Fifth Agreement."

00:08:20.160 --> 00:08:21.880 align:middle line:90%
Then it came out anyway.

00:08:21.880 --> 00:08:22.690 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:08:22.690 --> 00:08:24.370 align:middle line:84%
Can we talk about
"The Four Agreements"?

00:08:24.370 --> 00:08:26.668 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: Sure.

00:08:26.668 --> 00:08:28.210 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So the first
one is to always

00:08:28.210 --> 00:08:29.800 align:middle line:90%
be impeccable with your word.

00:08:29.800 --> 00:08:32.950 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Be impeccable
with the word.

00:08:32.950 --> 00:08:38.710 align:middle line:84%
Well, we need to understand
that we live in a story

00:08:38.710 --> 00:08:43.659 align:middle line:84%
that we create, and
that story is not real.

00:08:43.659 --> 00:08:45.530 align:middle line:90%
It's virtual.

00:08:45.530 --> 00:08:46.330 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's woven.

00:08:46.330 --> 00:08:48.670 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: Mm-hm.

00:08:48.670 --> 00:08:54.580 align:middle line:84%
We believe that we see
objects, but it's not true.

00:08:54.580 --> 00:08:57.070 align:middle line:90%
We perceive light.

00:08:57.070 --> 00:09:02.590 align:middle line:84%
The light that is coming
from those objects

00:09:02.590 --> 00:09:06.680 align:middle line:84%
hit the object, going into
our eye and project it.

00:09:06.680 --> 00:09:10.660 align:middle line:84%
And that is easy to prove
because right now if you

00:09:10.660 --> 00:09:13.420 align:middle line:84%
look around, you'll
see a lot of objects.

00:09:13.420 --> 00:09:17.600 align:middle line:84%
But as soon as you close your
eyes, everything disappear.

00:09:17.600 --> 00:09:19.600 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Your perception
of them disappears, yes.

00:09:19.600 --> 00:09:22.900 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Close your eyes,
everything disappear.

00:09:22.900 --> 00:09:26.890 align:middle line:84%
Open your eyes,
everything appear

00:09:26.890 --> 00:09:30.520 align:middle line:90%
because it's a projection.

00:09:30.520 --> 00:09:34.870 align:middle line:84%
But our mind, we
can say our brain

00:09:34.870 --> 00:09:38.730 align:middle line:84%
have the property to
make sense of everything,

00:09:38.730 --> 00:09:45.170 align:middle line:84%
and the mind is just a
reflection of what we perceive.

00:09:45.170 --> 00:09:45.970 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: True.

00:09:45.970 --> 00:09:51.160 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: But with the brain,
we just don't see the things,

00:09:51.160 --> 00:09:53.050 align:middle line:90%
we judge things.

00:09:53.050 --> 00:09:54.800 align:middle line:90%
We classify it.

00:09:54.800 --> 00:10:02.620 align:middle line:84%
We explain it, and we believe
that what we see is real.

00:10:02.620 --> 00:10:04.900 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, some of it
is, though, Don Miguel.

00:10:04.900 --> 00:10:06.470 align:middle line:90%
Some of the things are real.

00:10:06.470 --> 00:10:09.880 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Well, the ones that
is in your mind is not real.

00:10:09.880 --> 00:10:12.310 align:middle line:90%
It is just an image.

00:10:12.310 --> 00:10:15.700 align:middle line:84%
An image of a flower, then
that is outside of you.

00:10:15.700 --> 00:10:18.040 align:middle line:84%
You touch the
flower, that is real.

00:10:18.040 --> 00:10:21.820 align:middle line:84%
But the one that is in your
eyes, that is in your brain

00:10:21.820 --> 00:10:24.020 align:middle line:90%
is not real.

00:10:24.020 --> 00:10:31.660 align:middle line:84%
But you create from that image a
whole story, and in that story,

00:10:31.660 --> 00:10:34.090 align:middle line:90%
you are the main character.

00:10:34.090 --> 00:10:37.170 align:middle line:84%
You create everything,
and you fill it

00:10:37.170 --> 00:10:40.100 align:middle line:84%
with all the
secondary characters,

00:10:40.100 --> 00:10:44.110 align:middle line:84%
not just persons, but
objects, circumstances.

00:10:44.110 --> 00:10:46.780 align:middle line:84%
All the events that are
happening around you

00:10:46.780 --> 00:10:49.240 align:middle line:90%
is part of your story.

00:10:49.240 --> 00:10:55.090 align:middle line:84%
And everything that happen
to you, it really be

00:10:55.090 --> 00:10:57.830 align:middle line:90%
analyzed by what you believe.

00:10:57.830 --> 00:11:03.280 align:middle line:84%
You judge it, you qualify it,
and you store it in that way.

00:11:03.280 --> 00:11:04.830 align:middle line:90%
But it's already distort.

00:11:04.830 --> 00:11:06.730 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's the story
that we're storing.

00:11:06.730 --> 00:11:09.520 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: It is the story by the
domestication that we have.

00:11:09.520 --> 00:11:12.950 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, let's talk about
an extreme example, if we can.

00:11:12.950 --> 00:11:14.140 align:middle line:90%
A flower I understand.

00:11:14.140 --> 00:11:15.300 align:middle line:84%
You touch a flower,
and then you have

00:11:15.300 --> 00:11:16.425 align:middle line:90%
the perception of a flower.

00:11:16.425 --> 00:11:19.900 align:middle line:84%
But when you see something
like abuse, and then you see,

00:11:19.900 --> 00:11:25.490 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I hate animal abuse,
and I hate abusive people.

00:11:25.490 --> 00:11:29.100 align:middle line:84%
And when I close my
eyes, that still exists.

00:11:29.100 --> 00:11:32.590 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Yeah, but because
it's already in your brain.

00:11:32.590 --> 00:11:34.930 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: My perception
of it is real.

00:11:34.930 --> 00:11:36.350 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: Mm-hm.

00:11:36.350 --> 00:11:39.610 align:middle line:84%
Yes, but you have to
see that is the result

00:11:39.610 --> 00:11:41.890 align:middle line:90%
of all the domestication.

00:11:41.890 --> 00:11:47.480 align:middle line:84%
Because when you was growing up,
our parents say, this is bad,

00:11:47.480 --> 00:11:52.690 align:middle line:90%
this is Violence is not good.

00:11:52.690 --> 00:11:53.950 align:middle line:90%
It's abusive.

00:11:53.950 --> 00:11:56.140 align:middle line:90%
We qualified everything.

00:11:56.140 --> 00:12:00.070 align:middle line:84%
Then we already have
that in our mind.

