mean that because you

00:28:16.710 --> 00:28:19.080 align:middle line:84%
feel that you are more
intelligent than anybody else,

00:28:19.080 --> 00:28:20.980 align:middle line:90%
you don't believe what they say.

00:28:20.980 --> 00:28:22.830 align:middle line:90%
No, not at all.

00:28:22.830 --> 00:28:25.950 align:middle line:84%
You are skeptical
because you don't

00:28:25.950 --> 00:28:34.200 align:middle line:84%
take whatever they say is true
for them, but not true for you.

00:28:34.200 --> 00:28:36.462 align:middle line:84%
They give the message
according what they believe.

00:28:36.462 --> 00:28:37.920 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yes, their
beliefs systems.

00:28:37.920 --> 00:28:39.390 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: From whatever
they believe,

00:28:39.390 --> 00:28:44.430 align:middle line:84%
you can take what works
for you and push away

00:28:44.430 --> 00:28:47.420 align:middle line:90%
what it doesn't work for you.

00:28:47.420 --> 00:28:50.820 align:middle line:84%
That's why it's important
to learn, to listen.

00:28:50.820 --> 00:28:54.840 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: To be a compassionate
listener, but yet.

00:28:54.840 --> 00:28:58.117 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Yes, you listen
to what they say.

00:28:58.117 --> 00:28:59.700 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Is that what
you mean by that?

00:28:59.700 --> 00:29:00.700 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: Yes, you listen.

00:29:00.700 --> 00:29:02.220 align:middle line:90%
Whatever they say, you listen.

00:29:02.220 --> 00:29:05.520 align:middle line:84%
Many times almost from
the very beginning,

00:29:05.520 --> 00:29:08.130 align:middle line:84%
you know that you will not
get anything from there.

00:29:08.130 --> 00:29:10.010 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Isn't that
people pleasing?

00:29:10.010 --> 00:29:10.810 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: Hmm?

00:29:10.810 --> 00:29:12.690 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Isn't that
pleasing people?

00:29:12.690 --> 00:29:13.790 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: No, not really.

00:29:13.790 --> 00:29:14.590 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:29:14.590 --> 00:29:15.465 align:middle line:90%
There's a difference.

00:29:15.465 --> 00:29:17.520 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Because if they
hold your attention,

00:29:17.520 --> 00:29:20.790 align:middle line:90%
they will give a message to you.

00:29:20.790 --> 00:29:23.310 align:middle line:84%
Then you can make a
choice, you want to listen

00:29:23.310 --> 00:29:25.325 align:middle line:90%
or you don't want to listen.

00:29:25.325 --> 00:29:26.700 align:middle line:84%
But when you learn
to listen it's

00:29:26.700 --> 00:29:28.590 align:middle line:84%
because they really
hold your attention

00:29:28.590 --> 00:29:32.530 align:middle line:84%
and there's something that
could be good for you.

00:29:32.530 --> 00:29:33.330 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:29:33.330 --> 00:29:35.760 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: And you
hear what they say.

00:29:35.760 --> 00:29:37.410 align:middle line:90%
They can have great ideas.

00:29:37.410 --> 00:29:40.290 align:middle line:90%
OK, that works for me.

00:29:40.290 --> 00:29:44.520 align:middle line:84%
But then you also hear
superstitions, mm-hm,

00:29:44.520 --> 00:29:45.850 align:middle line:90%
and it doesn't work for you.

00:29:45.850 --> 00:29:48.720 align:middle line:84%
But you listen anyway,
and you respect it

00:29:48.720 --> 00:29:50.230 align:middle line:90%
because it's the way they are.

00:29:50.230 --> 00:29:51.150 align:middle line:90%
It's OK.

00:29:51.150 --> 00:29:54.060 align:middle line:84%
They can believe
whatever they want to.

00:29:54.060 --> 00:29:57.150 align:middle line:90%
It's not your problem.

00:29:57.150 --> 00:29:58.710 align:middle line:90%
They create their own story.

00:29:58.710 --> 00:30:01.110 align:middle line:84%
They're domesticated
in their own way.

00:30:01.110 --> 00:30:03.120 align:middle line:84%
They believe whatever
they believe.

00:30:03.120 --> 00:30:05.660 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't mean that it's
good or bad or right or wrong.

00:30:05.660 --> 00:30:08.640 align:middle line:90%
It's just a point of view.

00:30:08.640 --> 00:30:12.240 align:middle line:84%
When you reached
this fifth agreement,

00:30:12.240 --> 00:30:14.070 align:middle line:84%
you live with these
four agreements,

00:30:14.070 --> 00:30:17.910 align:middle line:84%
something very
interesting happen.

00:30:17.910 --> 00:30:23.160 align:middle line:84%
That will means that is
the end of your world,

00:30:23.160 --> 00:30:28.800 align:middle line:84%
the end of your reality,
because you no longer believe

00:30:28.800 --> 00:30:31.290 align:middle line:90%
all of that.

00:30:31.290 --> 00:30:32.630 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's freedom.

00:30:32.630 --> 00:30:33.590 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: Exactly.

00:30:33.590 --> 00:30:34.390 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:30:34.390 --> 00:30:36.100 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: You are completely free.

00:30:36.100 --> 00:30:41.280 align:middle line:90%
Then you becomes a master.

00:30:41.280 --> 00:30:46.230 align:middle line:84%
Imagine Jesus in
the desert 40 days

00:30:46.230 --> 00:30:50.710 align:middle line:90%
facing the snake, facing Satan.

00:30:50.710 --> 00:30:53.960 align:middle line:90%
Well, Satan has Jesus face.

00:30:53.960 --> 00:30:57.570 align:middle line:90%
He's facing Himself.

00:30:57.570 --> 00:31:02.320 align:middle line:84%
In 40 days, He no
longer believe,

00:31:02.320 --> 00:31:04.265 align:middle line:90%
but He listen everything.

00:31:04.265 --> 00:31:08.370 align:middle line:84%
And all the lies
goes completely away,

00:31:08.370 --> 00:31:14.890 align:middle line:84%
and now that Satan is
not a challenge anymore.

00:31:14.890 --> 00:31:15.690 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:31:15.690 --> 00:31:17.950 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: The one who
believes all your lies.

00:31:17.950 --> 00:31:18.750 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:31:18.750 --> 00:31:24.550 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Then Jesus face the
main character of Jesus's story,

00:31:24.550 --> 00:31:28.140 align:middle line:84%
and by the end, He
say, you are not real.

00:31:28.140 --> 00:31:30.955 align:middle line:90%
Same with Siddhartha.

00:31:30.955 --> 00:31:36.330 align:middle line:84%
Siddhartha is in the Bodhi
Tree, and he's facing Mara.

00:31:36.330 --> 00:31:41.850 align:middle line:84%
Mara is exactly the
same face as Siddhartha.

00:31:41.850 --> 00:31:46.170 align:middle line:84%
And by the end, he
say, you are not real.

00:31:46.170 --> 00:31:50.880 align:middle line:84%
The Earth is my witness,
you are not real.

00:31:50.880 --> 00:31:55.110 align:middle line:90%
Then he becomes Buddha.

00:31:55.110 --> 00:31:57.640 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So those are our demons,
those are our inner demons

00:31:57.640 --> 00:31:58.440 align:middle line:90%
that we face.

00:31:58.440 --> 00:32:02.340 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Well, we call it
demons, but it's really

00:32:02.340 --> 00:32:04.740 align:middle line:84%
the main character
of your story.

00:32:04.740 --> 00:32:07.560 align:middle line:90%
In my case, it was Miguel.

00:32:07.560 --> 00:32:12.240 align:middle line:90%
In your case, it's your name.

00:32:12.240 --> 00:32:16.120 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Did you discover this
when you had a heart attack?

00:32:16.120 --> 00:32:17.940 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: No, long before that.

00:32:17.940 --> 00:32:19.770 align:middle line:90%
Long, long before that.

00:32:19.770 --> 00:32:23.910 align:middle line:84%
I discovered that in
the time that I decide

00:32:23.910 --> 00:32:27.870 align:middle line:90%
to stop being a medical doctor.

00:32:27.870 --> 00:32:36.340 align:middle line:84%
When I decide to really go to
understand the human mind, just

00:32:36.340 --> 00:32:39.020 align:middle line:84%
to see if everybody
else was the same way

00:32:39.020 --> 00:32:42.500 align:middle line:90%
that I was at that time.

00:32:42.500 --> 00:32:44.570 align:middle line:90%
And we all are the same.

00:32:44.570 --> 00:32:45.440 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: We are?

00:32:45.440 --> 00:32:47.090 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Of course
we are the same.

00:32:47.090 --> 00:32:48.600 align:middle line:84%
The difference is
what we believe.

00:32:48.600 --> 00:32:49.400 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:32:49.400 --> 00:32:51.170 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: And it's not real.

00:32:51.170 --> 00:32:58.420 align:middle line:84%
Then our belief system, more
than 90% is nothing but lies,

00:32:58.420 --> 00:33:00.230 align:middle line:90%
misinterpretations.

00:33:00.230 --> 00:33:01.740 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Our demons are lies.

00:33:01.740 --> 00:33:03.900 align:middle line:90%
All of that is all made up.

00:33:03.900 --> 00:33:08.300 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: And that comes
from we can say the very

00:33:08.300 --> 00:33:13.730 align:middle line:90%
first distortion that we make.

00:33:13.730 --> 00:33:18.470 align:middle line:84%
Because what we
really are is love.

00:33:18.470 --> 00:33:20.030 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:33:20.030 --> 00:33:26.260 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: But we learn to love the
same way that our parents love,

00:33:26.260 --> 00:33:27.353 align:middle line:90%
the same way that--

00:33:27.353 --> 00:33:28.520 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Their parents loved.

00:33:28.520 --> 00:33:32.740 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: --Everybody
around us love.

00:33:32.740 --> 00:33:38.000 align:middle line:84%
And they love with
conditions, which

00:33:38.000 --> 00:33:43.490 align:middle line:84%
means I love you if
you let me control you.

00:33:43.490 --> 00:33:49.990 align:middle line:84%
If you let me control you, we
can be very happy all the time.

00:33:49.990 --> 00:33:51.250 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:33:51.250 --> 00:33:53.450 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: But if somebody
tells you, I love you,

00:33:53.450 --> 00:33:57.320 align:middle line:84%
you let me control you, you
will say, oh, wait a minute,

00:33:57.320 --> 00:34:00.560 align:middle line:90%
no one will control me.

00:34:00.560 --> 00:34:03.830 align:middle line:84%
But we want control
everybody, but we

00:34:03.830 --> 00:34:05.270 align:middle line:90%
don't want to be controlled.

00:34:05.270 --> 00:34:06.866 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Why does
human nature do that?

00:34:06.866 --> 00:34:08.449 align:middle line:84%
Why does human nature
need to control?

00:34:08.449 --> 00:34:12.699 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Because we learn, we
was domesticated that way.

00:34:12.699 --> 00:34:14.840 align:middle line:90%
And then that's the way we love.

00:34:14.840 --> 00:34:16.719 align:middle line:90%
I love you if.

00:34:16.719 --> 00:34:17.929 align:middle line:90%
That's the way they love us.

00:34:17.929 --> 00:34:21.590 align:middle line:84%
They love us if we
let them control us.

00:34:21.590 --> 00:34:24.949 align:middle line:84%
But the worst part
is that we learn

00:34:24.949 --> 00:34:28.730 align:middle line:84%
to love ourself
exactly the same way.

00:34:28.730 --> 00:34:33.920 align:middle line:84%
I love myself if, if
life becomes the way

00:34:33.920 --> 00:34:39.050 align:middle line:84%
I wish to be according
everybody else's opinions.

00:34:39.050 --> 00:34:41.449 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: If you have
that level of self-love,

00:34:41.449 --> 00:34:44.530 align:middle line:84%
you don't need that
validation so much.

00:34:44.530 --> 00:34:47.030 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Then when you
understand this point,

00:34:47.030 --> 00:34:51.889 align:middle line:84%
now you can understand easily
all the violence in the world,

00:34:51.889 --> 00:34:53.620 align:middle line:90%
you can understand war.

00:34:53.620 --> 00:34:57.440 align:middle line:84%
We can understand that
everybody's in a war of control

00:34:57.440 --> 00:35:00.140 align:middle line:90%
with everybody around them.

00:35:00.140 --> 00:35:04.700 align:middle line:84%
And even with themselves
they have that war of control

00:35:04.700 --> 00:35:10.310 align:middle line:84%
in their own mind because
they cannot control themselves

00:35:10.310 --> 00:35:12.240 align:middle line:90%
according of what they believe.

00:35:12.240 --> 00:35:13.040 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Believe in.

00:35:13.040 --> 00:35:15.200 align:middle line:84%
I've been looking at
the news with the hate

00:35:15.200 --> 00:35:17.360 align:middle line:90%
crimes that go on all the time.

00:35:17.360 --> 00:35:21.170 align:middle line:84%
And the people that are
committing these hate crimes

00:35:21.170 --> 00:35:23.480 align:middle line:84%
have these demons,
these inner demons,

00:35:23.480 --> 00:35:29.510 align:middle line:84%
or these resolutions that have
never been made and grievances,

00:35:29.510 --> 00:35:34.190 align:middle line:90%
and they cannot get beyond that.

00:35:34.190 --> 00:35:36.740 align:middle line:84%
And for the people
that it happens to,

00:35:36.740 --> 00:35:38.420 align:middle line:84%
you tell them not to
take it personally?

00:35:38.420 --> 00:35:39.980 align:middle line:84%
They're going to
tell you, yes, I'm

00:35:39.980 --> 00:35:40.745 align:middle line:90%
going to take this personally.

00:35:40.745 --> 00:35:42.870 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Well, that's
the only way they know.

00:35:42.870 --> 00:35:44.857 align:middle line:90%
This is OK.

00:35:44.857 --> 00:35:46.190 align:middle line:90%
There's nothing wrong with that.

00:35:46.190 --> 00:35:47.660 align:middle line:90%
It's OK.

00:35:47.660 --> 00:35:52.950 align:middle line:84%
But what is important at least
is to understand the point.

00:35:52.950 --> 00:35:59.000 align:middle line:84%
And a way you can see
that the result of that

00:35:59.000 --> 00:36:03.133 align:middle line:84%
is the creation of
those three questions.

00:36:03.133 --> 00:36:05.300 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: OK, so there's the
newest book that you have

00:36:05.300 --> 00:36:06.240 align:middle line:10%
called "The Three Questions."

00:36:06.240 --> 00:36:07.670 align:middle line:10%
>>RUIZ: "The Three Questions."

00:36:07.670 --> 00:36:09.950 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And it applies
to "The Four Agreements."

00:36:09.950 --> 00:36:16.280 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Oh, definitely,
because we can say our goal

00:36:16.280 --> 00:36:19.940 align:middle line:90%
or wish the way we want to be.

00:36:19.940 --> 00:36:23.770 align:middle line:84%
These are questions that
we have since millennials.

00:36:23.770 --> 00:36:25.250 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: A long time, yes.

00:36:25.250 --> 00:36:27.420 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: What am I?

00:36:27.420 --> 00:36:28.700 align:middle line:90%
What is real?

00:36:28.700 --> 00:36:30.207 align:middle line:90%
And what is love?

00:36:30.207 --> 00:36:31.790 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Those are
the three questions.

00:36:31.790 --> 00:36:33.080 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: The three questions.

00:36:33.080 --> 00:36:36.230 align:middle line:84%
And there are questions that
are changing all the time.

00:36:36.230 --> 00:36:37.920 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What am I?

00:36:37.920 --> 00:36:39.240 align:middle line:90%
What is real?

00:36:39.240 --> 00:36:40.040 align:middle line:90%
What is love?

00:36:40.040 --> 00:36:40.915 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: What is love?

00:36:40.915 --> 00:36:43.670 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So the answers to those
questions are ever changing?

00:36:43.670 --> 00:36:46.460 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Well, to
answer those questions,

00:36:46.460 --> 00:36:54.170 align:middle line:84%
we use the most wonderful tools,
which is these five agreements.

00:36:54.170 --> 00:36:56.970 align:middle line:84%
Then when we're using
these five agreements,

00:36:56.970 --> 00:36:59.120 align:middle line:90%
we are changing our reality.

00:36:59.120 --> 00:37:03.900 align:middle line:84%
But the reality is changing
anyway just by itself.

00:37:03.900 --> 00:37:06.800 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So if I'm
asking what is real,

00:37:06.800 --> 00:37:09.700 align:middle line:84%
I go back to the four
agreements and I say, well,

00:37:09.700 --> 00:37:11.120 align:middle line:90%
am I impeccable with my word?

00:37:11.120 --> 00:37:12.465 align:middle line:90%
Am I taking things personally?

00:37:12.465 --> 00:37:13.465 align:middle line:90%
Am I making assumptions?

00:37:13.465 --> 00:37:15.500 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Well, those
are the tools.

00:37:15.500 --> 00:37:17.030 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:37:17.030 --> 00:37:21.056 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: But to see what is real,
in order to get the answer,

00:37:21.056 --> 00:37:23.270 align:middle line:84%
first you have to
see what is not real.

00:37:23.270 --> 00:37:27.540 align:middle line:90%


00:37:27.540 --> 00:37:30.230 align:middle line:84%
And to answer what
is not real, now you

00:37:30.230 --> 00:37:31.580 align:middle line:90%
use these five agreements.

00:37:31.580 --> 00:37:32.850 align:middle line:90%
That's the tools.

00:37:32.850 --> 00:37:34.730 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Ah, I see.

00:37:34.730 --> 00:37:37.840 align:middle line:84%
Can you give me an example of
how this would work in life?

00:37:37.840 --> 00:37:44.120 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: OK, let's say
you are 12 years old, OK?

00:37:44.120 --> 00:37:47.510 align:middle line:90%
This is your reality.

00:37:47.510 --> 00:37:50.870 align:middle line:84%
In that reality, of
course you're real.

00:37:50.870 --> 00:37:53.780 align:middle line:84%
You have your name, everybody
tells you what you are,

00:37:53.780 --> 00:37:55.400 align:middle line:84%
and this is what
you believe you are.

00:37:55.400 --> 00:37:58.170 align:middle line:90%


00:37:58.170 --> 00:38:01.700 align:middle line:84%
Then that school
where you go is real,

00:38:01.700 --> 00:38:05.520 align:middle line:84%
your parents, your family is
real, all that is real for you.

00:38:05.520 --> 00:38:07.970 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: All the conditions
around you are real.

00:38:07.970 --> 00:38:11.680 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: And love is conditional.

00:38:11.680 --> 00:38:12.480 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:38:12.480 --> 00:38:14.065 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: Mm-hm.

00:38:14.065 --> 00:38:15.440 align:middle line:84%
Then using these
four agreements,

00:38:15.440 --> 00:38:17.860 align:middle line:84%
you are doubting
about all of that.

00:38:17.860 --> 00:38:18.660 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:38:18.660 --> 00:38:21.270 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Then when
a crisis happen,

00:38:21.270 --> 00:38:25.515 align:middle line:84%
something that is not
exactly what you want,

00:38:25.515 --> 00:38:26.930 align:middle line:90%
now you put in doubt.

00:38:26.930 --> 00:38:29.510 align:middle line:90%


00:38:29.510 --> 00:38:35.420 align:middle line:84%
Let's say you are in a
lecture, in a big conference.

00:38:35.420 --> 00:38:42.500 align:middle line:84%
All of a sudden, you go blank
in front of 1,000 people.

00:38:42.500 --> 00:38:44.990 align:middle line:84%
You just get out of
there, you go by yourself,

00:38:44.990 --> 00:38:47.480 align:middle line:84%
and now you start
judging yourself.

00:38:47.480 --> 00:38:52.790 align:middle line:84%
Look at why I do that,
why should I said that.

00:38:52.790 --> 00:38:53.790 align:middle line:90%
I'm this, I'm that.

00:38:53.790 --> 00:38:56.330 align:middle line:90%


00:38:56.330 --> 00:38:58.820 align:middle line:90%
You are judging yourself.

00:38:58.820 --> 00:39:01.880 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Mistake, embarrassment,
all of that happens.

00:39:01.880 --> 00:39:05.150 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: You feel that maybe
it is the end of the world.

00:39:05.150 --> 00:39:09.530 align:middle line:84%
How can everything keeps going
when this happened to you?

00:39:09.530 --> 00:39:11.850 align:middle line:90%


00:39:11.850 --> 00:39:12.650 align:middle line:90%
What am I?

00:39:12.650 --> 00:39:16.540 align:middle line:84%
I feel stupid, I'm this, I'm
that, et cetera, et cetera.

00:39:16.540 --> 00:39:18.290 align:middle line:84%
Well, with the four
agreements, I still

00:39:18.290 --> 00:39:23.210 align:middle line:84%
just say no and will
help you to recover

00:39:23.210 --> 00:39:24.560 align:middle line:90%
from that little crisis.

00:39:24.560 --> 00:39:25.950 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: My goodness.

00:39:25.950 --> 00:39:26.900 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:39:26.900 --> 00:39:30.903 align:middle line:84%
It would be catastrophic
in your mind otherwise.

00:39:30.903 --> 00:39:31.736 align:middle line:90%
And you can really--

00:39:31.736 --> 00:39:32.736 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: And you recover.

00:39:32.736 --> 00:39:33.650 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mm-hm.

00:39:33.650 --> 00:39:35.660 align:middle line:84%
You can work through it,
and these are the tools

00:39:35.660 --> 00:39:36.743 align:middle line:90%
on how to work through it.

00:39:36.743 --> 00:39:39.720 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: This crisis that
happened in our life.

00:39:39.720 --> 00:39:41.720 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Otherwise we would
say, well, what am I?

00:39:41.720 --> 00:39:42.590 align:middle line:90%
Well, I am stupid.

00:39:42.590 --> 00:39:44.215 align:middle line:84%
Well, you would use
the four agreements

00:39:44.215 --> 00:39:46.520 align:middle line:90%
to then override that and say

00:39:46.520 --> 00:39:48.170 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: Just had to say no.

00:39:48.170 --> 00:39:50.100 align:middle line:84%
It was just a
mistake or whatever.

00:39:50.100 --> 00:39:50.900 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't matter.

00:39:50.900 --> 00:39:53.540 align:middle line:90%


00:39:53.540 --> 00:39:56.150 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I can see this
different or whatever, yeah.

00:39:56.150 --> 00:39:59.450 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: And let's say that
we lost someone that we love.

00:39:59.450 --> 00:40:00.470 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:40:00.470 --> 00:40:01.490 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:40:01.490 --> 00:40:05.180 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Then how can
everything keeps going

00:40:05.180 --> 00:40:09.200 align:middle line:90%
when my husband, my son die?

00:40:09.200 --> 00:40:11.680 align:middle line:90%
It's very painful.

00:40:11.680 --> 00:40:14.330 align:middle line:90%
But is that real?

00:40:14.330 --> 00:40:16.130 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It looks real.

00:40:16.130 --> 00:40:18.795 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Is what religion
tell me is real,

00:40:18.795 --> 00:40:21.920 align:middle line:90%
what moral tell me is real?

00:40:21.920 --> 00:40:23.572 align:middle line:90%
Am I real?

00:40:23.572 --> 00:40:25.280 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, let's
take a great example.

00:40:25.280 --> 00:40:26.840 align:middle line:90%
So I lost my father.

00:40:26.840 --> 00:40:30.170 align:middle line:84%
And my parents were married
for almost 60 years,

00:40:30.170 --> 00:40:33.930 align:middle line:84%
and they were together
since they were 13.

00:40:33.930 --> 00:40:37.580 align:middle line:84%
They were the only
couple, that they only

00:40:37.580 --> 00:40:41.600 align:middle line:84%
knew each other for 60 years
in terms of being a couple.

00:40:41.600 --> 00:40:43.700 align:middle line:90%
They were bonded at the hip.

00:40:43.700 --> 00:40:46.100 align:middle line:84%
So my father's
passing has really

00:40:46.100 --> 00:40:50.010 align:middle line:84%
affected my mother, where she
feels that she's lost herself.

00:40:50.010 --> 00:40:50.810 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: Of course.

00:40:50.810 --> 00:40:53.810 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And this is very common
with people, who die shortly

00:40:53.810 --> 00:40:56.960 align:middle line:84%
after their loved ones,
because a whole piece of them

00:40:56.960 --> 00:40:57.850 align:middle line:90%
goes missing.

00:40:57.850 --> 00:40:58.650 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: Of course.

00:40:58.650 --> 00:41:00.560 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What could
I tell my mother?

00:41:00.560 --> 00:41:01.640 align:middle line:90%
Don't take it personally?

00:41:01.640 --> 00:41:02.047 align:middle line:90%
I can't.

00:41:02.047 --> 00:41:03.110 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: No.

00:41:03.110 --> 00:41:09.770 align:middle line:84%
Just love her just the
way she is, and it's OK.

00:41:09.770 --> 00:41:11.560 align:middle line:90%
That's all she needs, yes.

00:41:11.560 --> 00:41:13.880 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: She's wondering,
who am I without him?

00:41:13.880 --> 00:41:14.680 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: Exactly.

00:41:14.680 --> 00:41:16.760 align:middle line:90%


00:41:16.760 --> 00:41:19.170 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What do I tell her?

00:41:19.170 --> 00:41:22.400 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: You are always
you, and it's OK,

00:41:22.400 --> 00:41:24.700 align:middle line:90%
it's OK to have the pain.

00:41:24.700 --> 00:41:29.660 align:middle line:90%
It's OK to overcome whenever.

00:41:29.660 --> 00:41:32.750 align:middle line:84%
And to let her know
even if she understand

00:41:32.750 --> 00:41:39.650 align:middle line:84%
or not that, well, the image of
your father lives in her mind,

00:41:39.650 --> 00:41:42.100 align:middle line:84%
that she can keep
communicating with him,

00:41:42.100 --> 00:41:47.360 align:middle line:84%
talking to him knowing that the
body is gone because he doesn't

00:41:47.360 --> 00:41:51.860 align:middle line:84%
live anymore, but all the image
that she have for all those 60

00:41:51.860 --> 00:41:54.230 align:middle line:90%
years is still there.

00:41:54.230 --> 00:41:55.410 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes, very much.

00:41:55.410 --> 00:41:57.700 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: And of course,
she can hold his hand.

00:41:57.700 --> 00:41:59.390 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:41:59.390 --> 00:42:01.230 align:middle line:84%
That's the hardest
part is the touch.

00:42:01.230 --> 00:42:04.070 align:middle line:84%
It's the hardest part,
yeah, for everyone.

00:42:04.070 --> 00:42:08.630 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: She need to the touch,
but she do it in her own time.

00:42:08.630 --> 00:42:09.430 align:middle line:90%
It's OK.

00:42:09.430 --> 00:42:13.510 align:middle line:84%
Then the only thing is just
too love her, to support her.

00:42:13.510 --> 00:42:18.395 align:middle line:84%
It's OK, it's fine, and do
the best you can for her.

00:42:18.395 --> 00:42:21.320 align:middle line:90%


00:42:21.320 --> 00:42:26.420 align:middle line:84%
But that goes to
the third one, what

00:42:26.420 --> 00:42:32.990 align:middle line:84%
is love, because that would take
you for what you really are.

00:42:32.990 --> 00:42:40.100 align:middle line:84%
In order to answer that, you
need to see what love is not.

00:42:40.100 --> 00:42:42.170 align:middle line:90%
Is your jealousy love?

00:42:42.170 --> 00:42:45.050 align:middle line:90%
Is your control issues love?

00:42:45.050 --> 00:42:47.840 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I'm just thinking of
someone who maybe loses a child

00:42:47.840 --> 00:42:54.020 align:middle line:84%
or loses a sibling, and
they can't touch that child

00:42:54.020 --> 00:42:55.218 align:middle line:90%
or the sibling any longer.

00:42:55.218 --> 00:42:56.760 align:middle line:84%
And I was just about
to ask you that,

00:42:56.760 --> 00:42:59.960 align:middle line:84%
but you answered it to the
question of what is love.

00:42:59.960 --> 00:43:01.590 align:middle line:90%
Well, love is everlasting.

00:43:01.590 --> 00:43:02.390 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: Yes.

00:43:02.390 --> 00:43:03.530 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: The love of that child--

00:43:03.530 --> 00:43:04.400 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: Is eternal.

00:43:04.400 --> 00:43:05.570 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Eternal.

00:43:05.570 --> 00:43:07.850 align:middle line:84%
And the love of the
sibling is eternal.

00:43:07.850 --> 00:43:10.100 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: Love is life itself.

00:43:10.100 --> 00:43:10.900 align:middle line:90%
It's energy.

00:43:10.900 --> 00:43:13.840 align:middle line:90%
It's pure energy.

00:43:13.840 --> 00:43:15.830 align:middle line:90%
It's unconditional.

00:43:15.830 --> 00:43:20.210 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So can we love the
people that do the hate crimes?

00:43:20.210 --> 00:43:26.000 align:middle line:84%
Can we love the
wrongness in the world?

00:43:26.000 --> 00:43:30.860 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Well, we don't
have a choice, really.

00:43:30.860 --> 00:43:32.675 align:middle line:90%
We can judge them, and we do.

00:43:32.675 --> 00:43:33.800 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And we can get mad.

00:43:33.800 --> 00:43:34.400 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: Mm-hm.

00:43:34.400 --> 00:43:35.170 align:middle line:90%
And we do.

00:43:35.170 --> 00:43:35.970 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:43:35.970 --> 00:43:37.070 align:middle line:90%
And we can get angry.

00:43:37.070 --> 00:43:41.870 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: But you can do something
that could be very interesting.

00:43:41.870 --> 00:43:48.240 align:middle line:84%
You can get out and see
everything from the top.

00:43:48.240 --> 00:43:57.560 align:middle line:84%
You can see how humanity is only
one made by billions of people

00:43:57.560 --> 00:44:02.600 align:middle line:90%
and have a whole story.

00:44:02.600 --> 00:44:08.285 align:middle line:84%
Humanity has a beginning
and will have an end.

00:44:08.285 --> 00:44:14.630 align:middle line:84%
Then by seeing humanity
that way, you take one human

00:44:14.630 --> 00:44:19.490 align:middle line:84%
and you see the whole destiny
of humanity in only one human.

00:44:19.490 --> 00:44:21.890 align:middle line:84%
The whole steps you
see the one human.

00:44:21.890 --> 00:44:25.150 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So with all of humanity
and morality and immorality,

00:44:25.150 --> 00:44:26.230 align:middle line:90%
you see one human.

00:44:26.230 --> 00:44:27.030 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: Yes.

00:44:27.030 --> 00:44:27.905 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: From that perspective.

00:44:27.905 --> 00:44:29.510 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: From that perspective.

00:44:29.510 --> 00:44:33.620 align:middle line:84%
And you see that all humans
are exactly the same.

00:44:33.620 --> 00:44:38.250 align:middle line:84%
What will change is
what they believe.

00:44:38.250 --> 00:44:41.000 align:middle line:90%


00:44:41.000 --> 00:44:45.860 align:middle line:84%
We're born, we grow up,
we reproduce hopefully,

00:44:45.860 --> 00:44:49.090 align:middle line:90%
we get old, and we live.

00:44:49.090 --> 00:44:51.650 align:middle line:90%
We live through a body.

00:44:51.650 --> 00:44:58.160 align:middle line:84%
And the story also has a
beginning and has an end.

00:44:58.160 --> 00:45:00.710 align:middle line:90%


00:45:00.710 --> 00:45:04.460 align:middle line:84%
Then it begins
when the brain get

00:45:04.460 --> 00:45:10.610 align:middle line:84%
more mature that we can
hook with our attention,

00:45:10.610 --> 00:45:12.710 align:middle line:90%
we can create a whole reality.

00:45:12.710 --> 00:45:15.320 align:middle line:90%


00:45:15.320 --> 00:45:19.490 align:middle line:84%
But that will depends of
how the brain function.

00:45:19.490 --> 00:45:21.440 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Perceives
it, really, yes.

00:45:21.440 --> 00:45:25.370 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Because there may come
the day when the brain is no

00:45:25.370 --> 00:45:28.350 align:middle line:84%
longer good enough--
we can say it that way,

00:45:28.350 --> 00:45:31.250 align:middle line:90%
that's not exactly correct--

00:45:31.250 --> 00:45:34.610 align:middle line:84%
and then the reflections
are not the same,

00:45:34.610 --> 00:45:38.330 align:middle line:90%
the mind is not the same.

00:45:38.330 --> 00:45:42.980 align:middle line:90%
We can forget things.

00:45:42.980 --> 00:45:46.070 align:middle line:84%
Our mind is dissipating
little by little.

00:45:46.070 --> 00:45:51.230 align:middle line:84%
But at the moment that
the brain stop working,

00:45:51.230 --> 00:45:54.920 align:middle line:84%
we no longer reflect
the outside reality.

00:45:54.920 --> 00:45:57.590 align:middle line:90%
The mind is gone like that also.

00:45:57.590 --> 00:45:59.180 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting, yes.

00:45:59.180 --> 00:46:02.360 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: If you see
a mirror, everything

00:46:02.360 --> 00:46:05.180 align:middle line:84%
that is in the mirror
is a copy of everything

00:46:05.180 --> 00:46:13.140 align:middle line:84%
that is outside of the mirror,
but could be so clear that you

00:46:13.140 --> 00:46:13.940 align:middle line:90%
think it's real.

00:46:13.940 --> 00:46:15.770 align:middle line:84%
You want to touch
something, but you only

00:46:15.770 --> 00:46:17.120 align:middle line:84%
will touch the
surface of the mirror.

00:46:17.120 --> 00:46:18.412 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's a great example.

00:46:18.412 --> 00:46:21.100 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: It is exactly the same
that our eyes and our brain.

00:46:21.100 --> 00:46:22.150 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes, interesting.

00:46:22.150 --> 00:46:25.320 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: If you break the mirror,
it's not reflecting anything.

00:46:25.320 --> 00:46:26.510 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's shattered, yes.

00:46:26.510 --> 00:46:31.860 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Then when the
brain doesn't work anymore,

00:46:31.860 --> 00:46:35.130 align:middle line:84%
there's no more reflection,
there is no more mind.

00:46:35.130 --> 00:46:41.480 align:middle line:84%
The mind is gone, but
the body can still alive.

00:46:41.480 --> 00:46:45.020 align:middle line:90%


00:46:45.020 --> 00:46:47.530 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's all about
changing your perception.

00:46:47.530 --> 00:46:48.970 align:middle line:84%
It takes strength
to do something

00:46:48.970 --> 00:46:50.428 align:middle line:84%
like this, a
different perspective.

00:46:50.428 --> 00:46:55.460 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Your reason is gone,
the judgments are gone,

00:46:55.460 --> 00:46:57.325 align:middle line:90%
belief system is gone.

00:46:57.325 --> 00:46:58.700 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And you're
a clean slate.

00:46:58.700 --> 00:47:02.540 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: But your
body can still alive.

00:47:02.540 --> 00:47:06.090 align:middle line:84%
And that may happen to many
of us after certain age.

00:47:06.090 --> 00:47:08.900 align:middle line:90%


00:47:08.900 --> 00:47:10.490 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: There is
a great video here

00:47:10.490 --> 00:47:13.880 align:middle line:84%
I want you to take a look
at talking about humanity,

00:47:13.880 --> 00:47:16.520 align:middle line:84%
and it really could
be the solution

00:47:16.520 --> 00:47:17.870 align:middle line:90%
on how to change the world.

00:47:17.870 --> 00:47:20.670 align:middle line:84%
Look at Don Miguel
talking about this.

00:47:20.670 --> 00:47:27.420 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: I come with you
to asking you a favor,

00:47:27.420 --> 00:47:34.518 align:middle line:84%
and the favor is, please
help me to change the world.

00:47:34.518 --> 00:47:36.938 align:middle line:90%
[APPLAUSE]

00:47:36.938 --> 00:47:39.850 align:middle line:90%


00:47:39.850 --> 00:47:44.420 align:middle line:84%
And I don't refer to
the world of humanity.

00:47:44.420 --> 00:47:48.840 align:middle line:84%
I mean the world
that you create,

00:47:48.840 --> 00:47:55.410 align:middle line:84%
your own creation, your world
that is only true for you,

00:47:55.410 --> 00:47:59.320 align:middle line:90%
but for nobody else.

00:47:59.320 --> 00:48:03.440 align:middle line:84%
You create the
story of your life.

00:48:03.440 --> 00:48:09.410 align:middle line:84%
You create an entire reality
that is only true for you.

00:48:09.410 --> 00:48:14.920 align:middle line:84%
There is 6 billion people in
the world on this planet Earth,

00:48:14.920 --> 00:48:20.590 align:middle line:84%
6 billion people who
create their own story.

00:48:20.590 --> 00:48:28.060 align:middle line:84%
I can say 6 billions of artists
because we all are artists.

00:48:28.060 --> 00:48:30.960 align:middle line:90%
We create.

00:48:30.960 --> 00:48:39.350 align:middle line:84%
I create my personal world,
the world of Don Miguel Ruiz.

00:48:39.350 --> 00:48:41.960 align:middle line:90%
It's just a story.

00:48:41.960 --> 00:48:44.480 align:middle line:90%
It's not even real.

00:48:44.480 --> 00:48:46.580 align:middle line:90%
And by the way, it's not true.

00:48:46.580 --> 00:48:49.920 align:middle line:90%


00:48:49.920 --> 00:48:55.110 align:middle line:84%
Like your story is
not true either,

00:48:55.110 --> 00:48:57.770 align:middle line:90%
but you believe it's true.

00:48:57.770 --> 00:49:04.190 align:middle line:84%
You create your own story,
and we live in that story.

00:49:04.190 --> 00:49:07.610 align:middle line:84%
It's so perfect that we
don't notice that we live

00:49:07.610 --> 00:49:11.420 align:middle line:90%
in the story that we create.

00:49:11.420 --> 00:49:18.410 align:middle line:84%
In that story, we create
multiple secondary characters.

00:49:18.410 --> 00:49:21.630 align:middle line:84%
Every person that you
know and many others

00:49:21.630 --> 00:49:25.270 align:middle line:84%
that you don't know, but you
know about them, all of them

00:49:25.270 --> 00:49:29.080 align:middle line:84%
are part of the
world in your world.

00:49:29.080 --> 00:49:32.620 align:middle line:84%
But the most important
part in your creation

00:49:32.620 --> 00:49:42.020 align:middle line:84%
is the main character, and
that main character is you.

00:49:42.020 --> 00:49:44.630 align:middle line:84%
You create the main
character of your story,

00:49:44.630 --> 00:49:48.890 align:middle line:84%
and the whole
story is about you.

00:49:48.890 --> 00:49:52.360 align:middle line:84%
In my story, the main
character is Miguel Ruiz.

00:49:52.360 --> 00:49:54.910 align:middle line:90%


00:49:54.910 --> 00:49:57.920 align:middle line:90%
But he's just a character.

00:49:57.920 --> 00:49:59.750 align:middle line:90%
He's not even real.

00:49:59.750 --> 00:50:02.160 align:middle line:90%
It's not true.

00:50:02.160 --> 00:50:04.440 align:middle line:84%
But my whole story
is about Miguel Ruiz.

00:50:04.440 --> 00:50:06.520 align:middle line:84%
It's how Miguel Ruiz
perceive everything.

00:50:06.520 --> 00:50:08.875 align:middle line:84%
It's about how Miguel Ruiz
believe about everything

00:50:08.875 --> 00:50:09.675 align:middle line:90%
he believes.

00:50:09.675 --> 00:50:12.190 align:middle line:90%


00:50:12.190 --> 00:50:15.950 align:middle line:84%
But it's just his point of
view, and that point of view

00:50:15.950 --> 00:50:18.660 align:middle line:90%
is changing all the time.

00:50:18.660 --> 00:50:22.080 align:middle line:84%
Just like in your own
story, your point of view

00:50:22.080 --> 00:50:24.990 align:middle line:90%
is changing all the time.

00:50:24.990 --> 00:50:26.370 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That is so true.

00:50:26.370 --> 00:50:31.110 align:middle line:84%
So how can we
create a new story?

00:50:31.110 --> 00:50:33.750 align:middle line:84%
How can we do that if we
really already created

00:50:33.750 --> 00:50:36.090 align:middle line:90%
this life as our story?

00:50:36.090 --> 00:50:38.100 align:middle line:90%
So can we recreate it?

00:50:38.100 --> 00:50:39.210 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: Oh, definitely.

00:50:39.210 --> 00:50:40.560 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: The way we want to?

00:50:40.560 --> 00:50:41.360 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: Definitely.

00:50:41.360 --> 00:50:42.943 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's the
whole point, right?

00:50:42.943 --> 00:50:44.340 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: Exactly.

00:50:44.340 --> 00:50:48.690 align:middle line:84%
After the fifth agreement,
where you no longer believe

00:50:48.690 --> 00:50:55.500 align:middle line:84%
all your lies, when you learn
to respect yourself completely

00:50:55.500 --> 00:50:58.480 align:middle line:84%
and you can respect everybody
around you completely

00:50:58.480 --> 00:51:02.880 align:middle line:84%
and accept them just
the way they are,

00:51:02.880 --> 00:51:05.260 align:middle line:90%
now your story is different.

00:51:05.260 --> 00:51:10.350 align:middle line:84%
And now you, the main
character of your story,

00:51:10.350 --> 00:51:13.850 align:middle line:90%
it becomes an ally.

00:51:13.850 --> 00:51:18.570 align:middle line:84%
It's helping you to live
in this personal paradise

00:51:18.570 --> 00:51:20.810 align:middle line:90%
that you just create.

00:51:20.810 --> 00:51:25.450 align:middle line:84%
And you no longer really
belongs to everybody around you,

00:51:25.450 --> 00:51:27.240 align:middle line:90%
but you understand them.

00:51:27.240 --> 00:51:30.270 align:middle line:84%
They will not understand
you, but it's not important

00:51:30.270 --> 00:51:32.590 align:middle line:90%
if they understand you or not.

00:51:32.590 --> 00:51:35.040 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So if somebody is
sick and they're creating,

00:51:35.040 --> 00:51:38.250 align:middle line:84%
that's essentially a story
that they're creating

00:51:38.250 --> 00:51:40.740 align:middle line:90%
of a sickness, of a sick body?

00:51:40.740 --> 00:51:44.390 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Well, the
body gets sick.

00:51:44.390 --> 00:51:48.286 align:middle line:84%
Even if we don't want to,
the body will get sick.

00:51:48.286 --> 00:51:50.330 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Hmm, interesting.

00:51:50.330 --> 00:51:52.550 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: When all the
organs start failing,

00:51:52.550 --> 00:51:54.260 align:middle line:90%
the body will get sick.

00:51:54.260 --> 00:51:57.480 align:middle line:84%
If we get an infection,
the body will get sick.

00:51:57.480 --> 00:52:00.320 align:middle line:84%
If we have an accident,
we break the spine,

00:52:00.320 --> 00:52:02.630 align:middle line:90%
the body will be sick.

00:52:02.630 --> 00:52:07.670 align:middle line:90%
2002 I have a heart attack.

00:52:07.670 --> 00:52:08.740 align:middle line:90%
I almost die.

00:52:08.740 --> 00:52:10.770 align:middle line:90%
I was nine weeks in coma.

00:52:10.770 --> 00:52:11.570 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:52:11.570 --> 00:52:17.360 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: I come back, and my body
was not the same any longer.

00:52:17.360 --> 00:52:21.270 align:middle line:84%
My body was in
pain all the time.

00:52:21.270 --> 00:52:23.780 align:middle line:90%
Nobody noticed.

00:52:23.780 --> 00:52:26.630 align:middle line:84%
They didn't know that
my body was in pain.

00:52:26.630 --> 00:52:29.210 align:middle line:90%


00:52:29.210 --> 00:52:33.890 align:middle line:90%
But I want to live and to enjoy.

00:52:33.890 --> 00:52:37.070 align:middle line:84%
I knew that my body
was like an old car,

00:52:37.070 --> 00:52:40.970 align:middle line:84%
but it's taking me
any place I want to.

00:52:40.970 --> 00:52:44.780 align:middle line:84%
And I had so much
love for this body.

00:52:44.780 --> 00:52:48.200 align:middle line:84%
I take care of my
body the best I can.

00:52:48.200 --> 00:52:53.240 align:middle line:84%
Doctors tell me that I may
live one year, maybe two years.

00:52:53.240 --> 00:52:57.440 align:middle line:84%
Well, it was almost
seven, eight years.

00:52:57.440 --> 00:52:58.630 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Long ago, yes.

00:52:58.630 --> 00:53:02.630 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: And I decide
to have a new heart.

00:53:02.630 --> 00:53:05.558 align:middle line:90%
Then I have a new heart.

00:53:05.558 --> 00:53:07.350 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You got an
entire heart transplant.

00:53:07.350 --> 00:53:09.890 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Yes, in 2010, I
have a heart transplant,

00:53:09.890 --> 00:53:12.360 align:middle line:90%
eight years later.

00:53:12.360 --> 00:53:17.320 align:middle line:84%
And now it's 2009 and I'm
still in my physical body.

00:53:17.320 --> 00:53:22.610 align:middle line:84%
And yes, my body's
been sick, but we all

00:53:22.610 --> 00:53:24.898 align:middle line:84%
will die for one
reason or another.

00:53:24.898 --> 00:53:26.856 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But you don't
create a story around it.

00:53:26.856 --> 00:53:30.440 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: Of course I'm not.

00:53:30.440 --> 00:53:37.885 align:middle line:84%
I didn't create the bones of
my body, and nobody really do.

00:53:37.885 --> 00:53:40.970 align:middle line:84%
They chastised them so many
times because they get sick.

00:53:40.970 --> 00:53:44.420 align:middle line:90%
Well, so what?

00:53:44.420 --> 00:53:47.300 align:middle line:84%
If I can live the way I can
live, someone with cancer

00:53:47.300 --> 00:53:52.810 align:middle line:84%
can live with that cancer until
the body just kick him out.

00:53:52.810 --> 00:53:54.740 align:middle line:90%
It's OK.

00:53:54.740 --> 00:53:56.820 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: To not create
a story around it.

00:53:56.820 --> 00:53:57.620 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: Yeah.

00:53:57.620 --> 00:54:01.100 align:middle line:90%
And let's say that we are sick.

00:54:01.100 --> 00:54:06.120 align:middle line:84%
It's nobody's fault,
not even our fault.

00:54:06.120 --> 00:54:08.570 align:middle line:84%
There's no one to
blame about for that.

00:54:08.570 --> 00:54:11.420 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I want to apply this to
everything, so money, finances.

00:54:11.420 --> 00:54:14.390 align:middle line:84%
Say someone is devastated,
financially broke,

00:54:14.390 --> 00:54:16.880 align:middle line:90%
can't make ends meet.

00:54:16.880 --> 00:54:18.500 align:middle line:84%
Are they creating
a story around it?

00:54:18.500 --> 00:54:21.470 align:middle line:84%
Or could it be the circumstances
that made that happen?

00:54:21.470 --> 00:54:25.180 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Well, let's say
that they make choices,

00:54:25.180 --> 00:54:28.790 align:middle line:84%
and those choices
have repercussions.

00:54:28.790 --> 00:54:32.090 align:middle line:84%
It's the result of
choices they made.

00:54:32.090 --> 00:54:35.750 align:middle line:84%
Let's say that someone
got addicted going

00:54:35.750 --> 00:54:40.940 align:middle line:90%
to alcohol or anything else.

00:54:40.940 --> 00:54:43.310 align:middle line:84%
The result will be that
sooner or later, they will

00:54:43.310 --> 00:54:47.230 align:middle line:90%
lose whatever they had before.

00:54:47.230 --> 00:54:51.170 align:middle line:84%
But it's a result
of their decisions.

00:54:51.170 --> 00:54:53.540 align:middle line:90%
There's no one to blame.

00:54:53.540 --> 00:54:55.490 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So did they
create a story around it?

00:54:55.490 --> 00:54:57.620 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: Of course they
create all the stories.

00:54:57.620 --> 00:54:59.430 align:middle line:90%
They blame everybody else.

00:54:59.430 --> 00:55:00.230 align:middle line:90%
It was not me.

00:55:00.230 --> 00:55:01.850 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And believe the stories.

00:55:01.850 --> 00:55:04.620 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: They believe it,
of course, which is OK.

00:55:04.620 --> 00:55:08.590 align:middle line:84%
There's nothing wrong
with that because it's

00:55:08.590 --> 00:55:10.970 align:middle line:90%
in our nature we create stories.

00:55:10.970 --> 00:55:12.890 align:middle line:90%
We are storytellers.

00:55:12.890 --> 00:55:15.500 align:middle line:90%
We are dreaming all the time.

00:55:15.500 --> 00:55:18.590 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Until you
rise above it and get

00:55:18.590 --> 00:55:21.710 align:middle line:84%
into a different
perspective, and then you

00:55:21.710 --> 00:55:24.410 align:middle line:84%
start to look at, as
you said in that video,

00:55:24.410 --> 00:55:27.040 align:middle line:90%
we are the artists of our story.

00:55:27.040 --> 00:55:28.080 align:middle line:90%
>>RUIZ: Exactly.

00:55:28.080 --> 00:55:31.290 align:middle line:84%
And we have the
instruments to do it.

00:55:31.290 --> 00:55:33.500 align:middle line:84%
We have the four
agreements, and we

00:55:33.500 --> 00:55:36.390 align:middle line:84%
see what we want to paint,
what we want to create,

00:55:36.390 --> 00:55:39.320 align:middle line:90%
which is this three questions.

00:55:39.320 --> 00:55:40.940 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Constantly
recreating, that's

00:55:40.940 --> 00:55:42.107 align:middle line:90%
how you recreate your story.

00:55:42.107 --> 00:55:43.820 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: It's changing
all the time.

00:55:43.820 --> 00:55:46.858 align:middle line:84%
Then the answer of that
question when you have 12

00:55:46.858 --> 00:55:48.900 align:middle line:84%
will be different than
the answer of the question

00:55:48.900 --> 00:55:54.650 align:middle line:84%
when you are 16, then
when you just get married,

00:55:54.650 --> 00:55:55.910 align:middle line:90%
when you have your children.

00:55:55.910 --> 00:55:58.430 align:middle line:90%


00:55:58.430 --> 00:56:01.120 align:middle line:84%
All those questions keeps
changing and changing.

00:56:01.120 --> 00:56:03.830 align:middle line:84%
It's not the same,
but it's guiding you

00:56:03.830 --> 00:56:05.983 align:middle line:84%
in certain directions
of your creation.

00:56:05.983 --> 00:56:07.400 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Those are
great questions.

00:56:07.400 --> 00:56:10.530 align:middle line:84%
>>RUIZ: But you have the tools
to go into whatever directions

00:56:10.530 --> 00:56:11.330 align:middle line:90%
you're going.

00:56:11.330 --> 00:56:13.280 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: To continue to ask.

00:56:13.280 --> 00:56:15.605 align:middle line:84%
I have to ask, through
all you have been through,

00:56:15.605 --> 00:56:19.400 align:middle line:84%
through the heart attack and the
heart transplant and everything

00:56:19.400 --> 00:56:23.810 align:middle line:84%
that you've written
about, what fuels you?

00:56:23.810 --> 00:56:30.860 align:middle line:84%
